13/04/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Mayoral candidates in Tirana are promising to boost the economy if elected on May 8th. Incumbent Mayor Edi Rama attended a public meeting Tuesday (April 12th), where he presented a plan for a "European Tirana" that he says would boost residents' quality of life. Rama, head of the biggest opposition Socialist Party, discussed projects that are currently under way and their importance to urban development. 
Main opponent Lulzim Basha, a candidate of the ruling coalition, promised that measures such as reducing taxes and creating incentives for businesses would create 10,000 new jobs in the capital. (Shekulli, Balkan Web, Top Channel, Lajmifundit - 12/04/11)
